  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds arguments used to clone and customize a typeface.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a lightweight `ref struct` that bundles the arguments
used to customize a typeface when cloning it via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>.

Set one or more of its properties — variation design position, collection
index, palette index, or palette overrides — then pass it to `Clone` to
produce a new typeface with those settings applied.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a variable typeface at a custom weight axis position.
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
        {
            Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
            Value = 700f,
        }
    },
};

using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
